Package org.aksw.deer.logging

Class MdcThreadPoolExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.AbstractExecutorService
      • java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool
        • org.aksw.deer.logging.MdcThreadPoolExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Executor, ExecutorService

    public class MdcThreadPoolExecutor
extends ForkJoinPool
    A SLF4J MDC-compatible ForkJoinPool.

    In general, MDC is used to store diagnostic information (e.g. a user's session id) in per-thread variables, to facilitate logging. However, although MDC data is passed to thread children, this doesn't work when threads are reused in a thread pool. This is a drop-in replacement for ForkJoinPool sets MDC data before each task appropriately.
